results.name: Largest eight-digit primes (in decreasing order) which use each of 0-to-7 decimal digits exactly once.
comment: There are exactly 2668 eight-digit primes using digits 0-to-7 exactly once, here the largest ones are given; cf. A109177 with the smallest ones.
results.author: _Zak Seidov_, Jun 21 2005
